-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261836\">The seat stays are braced, but that brace is connector here for some as-of-yet unknown reason</figcaption></figure><p>Connecting that triad of pivots to the rocker is what looks to be a CNC machined brace plate that itself has two potential upper mounting points. These likely alter the leverage curve slightly and allow Commencal and their riders to experiment with different setups quickly using the same parts.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed.jpg\" alt=\"commencal supreme 