ent/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a></p><p>This is not the only point at which adjustments can be made. Note the rear dropouts are elongated, possibly allowing for chainstay length adjustment. The chainring may also be hiding a flip-chip at the lower shock mount.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg\" alt=\"commencal supreme dh chain idler fixed position\" width=\"1200\" height=\"798\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-632x420.jpg 632w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb18 src ng ngcb18 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a></p><p>Welded to the base of the seat tube, just above what might normally be considered the “main pivot” (sitting just behind the chain ring), is the aluminium plate that supports the chain idler. On the current production <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/07/02/commencal-supreme-mullet-downhill-bike-lets-amaury-pierron-do-the-talking/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Supreme</a>, the idler’s position changes as the bike goes through its rear wheel travel as it is bolted to the rear swingarm.</p><p>However, on the prototype we see here its position does not change as the bike goes through its travel. Here, it is largely responsible for isolating drivetrain forces from the suspension in a bid to reduce, or even eradicate, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/09/18/aasq-85-what-is-pedal-kick-back-full-suspension-chain-growth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">pedal kickback</a>.</p><figure id=\"attachment_261839\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-261839\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-